            {
                "s2_paper_id": "a2ce2b3cbc7fb5b4f3acad725c5bb0da30e88a6e",
                "title": "The Price of Security: The Challenge of Measuring Business Value Investments in Securing Information Systems",
                "year": 2015,
                "venue": "Communications of the IIMA",
                "citation_count": 5,
                "reference_count": 15,
                "abstract": "With powerful regulations surrounding security and privacy of information, the authors attempt to identify challenges valuing information security investments. The authors examine three primary approaches to measuring information value: Perceived, Real, and Normative. Literature is reviewed and the approaches are examined in terms of their strengths and weaknesses in providing value measurements for secure information systems. A framework is presented to suggest at what level in an organization and in what situations these information value approaches are most suitable.",
                "authors": [
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "40558275",
